<TABLE BORDER=0 cellpadding=4 border=0 cellspacing=1 WIDTH="95%"><TR bgcolor="#D5E6E1"><TD COLSPAN=2><CENTER><FONT SIZE="2" COLOR="#000080" FACE="Verdana, Arial">T O P I C  &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; R E V I E W</font></CENTER></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">kyle</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">I like being unique…<P>I was wandering around Firiona Vie last night, and let me tell you, an Erudite Cleric in Quest Armor, carrying a CGS and a Tome of Spirit, gets some second glances. 	<P>For those that don’t know, the Tome of Spirit has that “open book” appearance (not the “closed book” with the little handle, which I think is sort of silly looking) and can be equipped in the _weapon_ hand. It is +6 Wis and +6 Int. It actually belongs to my enchanter friend, but I have more use for it on a day to day basis, so he’s being kind enough to let me borrow it. (He has charisma items so only needs these particular stat boosts when he works on his jewel craft.) Does anyone know how rare this item is? I was only half paying attention when my friend got it from a library somewhere in Kunark and I don’t see it listed on Everlore yet.<P>Also, does anyone know anything definitive about the max Wisdom being 200? I have read that it is, in fact, the practical limit and there’s no point in going over it, and also that for Wis casters, there is no practical limit so it makes sense to get more Wis items even after you hit 200. I think the high level Wis casters on my server (Brell Serillis) are more inclined to believe that latter, since many of them have crazy amounts of Wis gear; far more than they would need just to get to 200. <P>Gilt Helamakir<BR>35th Level Cleric of Quellious, Brell Serillis<BR></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Rinkee</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">While I am afraid that I do not have any information on the Tome, I do know about the wis cap.  It is a hard cap where each +wis point over 200 gives you +1 mana.  This means that going over 200 wis is more or less uselss - people usually try and swap out some items for either some good AC or +mana items.  Its the same for caster and priest classes, and will likely not be changed in the near future.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Kruass</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Woohoo.  Thanks for posting on wether the spirit tome was open book or closed book.  I couldn't seem to confirm/deny the rumor I had heard about it since nobody seems to have one on Povar (well nobody above level 45, since my circle of acquaintences ends below there).<P>:)<P>------------------<BR>Kruass, Cleric, Povar.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Cal</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Prolly from Kaesora, from the Spectral Librarian. You go down. Simple as that. No ramps, no ladders. You just go down. Once you're in and take one of the 3 passages, you better have someone to evac you or you had better have gate.<P>A green mob to a 46 was hitting for close to 80.. and a rumour (I can't confirm this), is that there are mobs that hit for 90's bunched very close together.<P>I wanted this book for my cleric to... but he'll survive with the nifty robe. Shame my necromancer can't wear that.  <IMG SRC="http://eqcleric.gameglow.com/ubb/smile.gif"></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">kitsinu</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">More than 200 Wisdom would be great for trade skills.  Wisdom affects how often you suceed while Intelligence affects how fast you gain skill.  Once you are at trivial on an item, or max skill, you want Wisdom to make things.  Enchanters the best Jewelers?  Nope, Clerics are if they can get the metal.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Foahr Decator</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">yes there is a way out of Keaora well from the left pit.<BR>go in till you hit the pits drop down the lelf pit go right then right then left then down thew the broken floor. there are 2 passage wasy from there 1 to and undea area one goes out kind of.<BR>take the path that goes down then back up you come to a room with a spirl ramp you close to out now. go up and thew and one of the pasages on the right will be or lead to a pit which when takeen will lead you back to where you came in to the first 2 pits. <BR>bring enchanter and a druid or wiz or alot of fire power bc it can go all bad with a runner or if you get 2 or 3 rommers(fyi this place has lots of romers). <BR>     theis are probly bad directions but i give bad directions. good luck if you want to go 40 41sk and me a 40 cleic is what i had when i went in and if we did not get cocky we would of been fine with the spiders sperms and the odd undead but we didnt splat. we just could not find a room to pull to where there where no rommers or room pops we just killed moved killed moved till we hit the undead area and sead "thats too much it will all kill us" and it did.<BR>__________________<BR>Foahr Decator<BR>40 cleric on Rathe<BR>__________________<P>p.s. corpse recovry is a pain^2<BR></FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>
